condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :LA, Section II, A | Description :Borrower to monitor and evaluate progress and prepare Project Reports. Eachreport to cover 6 month periods, due March 1 & Sept. 1,starting Sept. 1, 2011. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :LA, Section II, B | Description :Borrower to have its Financial Statements audited annually, and submit auditedFS to the Bank not later than six months after the end of the period. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Section I C, para 3(a) | Description :Project participants & companies to monitor and evaluateimplementation of EMPs, RAPs, RPF, Dam Safety Plan & remedial works at dam sites and submit reports semiannually starting Sept 1,2011 | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Section I C, para 3(b) | Description :Submit by March 1 (starting 2012) annual reports on results of M&Eactivities for Dam Safety Plan and any remedial works | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Section IV, para 1 (b) | Description :Commence implementation of the action plans referred to in para 1(a)above | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :PA, Section IV, para 1(a) | Description :Project participants to furnish to the Bank a time-bound O&M actionplan | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Section IV, para 2(a) | Description :Furnish to Bank by Sept, starting 2012, audited financial statementsrelated to water supply or waste water operations and financial projections | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA, Section IV, para 2(b) | Description :Jiande City to furnish to Bank by Sept 1 starting 2012, financialreport covering costs & revenues from solid waste ops and financial projections for project company | Frequency :Yearly
